com.nnetworks.jopa
Class Processor

java.lang.Object
  com.nnetworks.jopa.Processor
Direct Known Subclasses:
com.nnetworks.jopa.PERSES.PERSES, Processor_PSP, com.nnetworks.jopa.UDAV.UDAV, com.nnetworks.jopa.WEBDAV.WEBDAV
public class Processor
extends java.lang.Object

Serves as the base for various access methods implementation. This class encapsulates common functionality for JOPA access methods, like WebDAV, OWA, etc. All actual methods extend this class and add actual request service implementation.

getArrayDescriptor

protected oracle.sql.ArrayDescriptor getArrayDescriptor(java.lang.String sArrayTypeName)
                                                 throws java.sql.SQLException
Creates an ArrayDescriptor for array type. Supported array types are SQL collections, PL/SQL tables are not supported by the Thin JDBC driver, hence they are not supported here either, SQLException will be thrown for such array types.

Parameters:
sArrayTypeName - Oracle array type name (fully qualified or short)
Returns:
array descriptor for the specified array type
Throws:
java.sql.SQLException - when array descriptor cannot be created
